  ## Skills to Use
  
  **How skills work:** Claude Code auto-discovers skills from `.claude/skills/` at session start. Skill descriptions are visible automatically — full content loads when relevant context triggers invocation. You can also force-load a skill's full content by reading its file directly: `Read .claude/skills/{skill-name}/SKILL.md`
  
  **Always ensure `openclaw-debugger` is active first** — layer-specific references, config blocks, troubleshooting. If it hasn't auto-invoked, force-load: `Read .claude/skills/openclaw-debugger/SKILL.md`
  
  | Layer | Additional Skills | Why |
  |---|---|---|
  | L1 | — | debugger covers gateway, sandbox, hooks |
  | L2 | — | debugger covers model cascade, agents, env |
  | L3 | `openclaw-telegram-bot-skill`, `openclaw-pipeline-creator` | Telegram API, pipeline custom commands |
  | L4 | `openclaw-context-engineer`, `drift-guardian` | Context file authoring, token budgets, persona drift prevention |
  | L5 | `drift-guardian`, `engineering-system-design` | Drift prevention, routing architecture |
  | L6 | `openclaw-pipeline-creator`, `skill-creator`, `mcp-builder`, `engineering-code-review` | Pipeline YAML, skill authoring, MCP servers |
  | L7 | `openclaw-context-engineer`, `operations-process-optimization` | MEMORY.md curation, audit log design |
  
