  ### ALL LAYERS — Cross-Layer-Notes Cleanup
  
  **Applies to:** L1–L7 (every layer has a `cross-layer-notes.md`)
  
  **Do this FIRST on each layer before any other tasks.**
  
  1. Read `stack/L[X]-[name]/cross-layer-notes.md`
  2. **Delete all resolved notes.** The changelog already has the history. Resolved notes are dead weight.
  3. **Mark tracked notes.** Any open note that has a matching task ID in session-prompt.md, update its status to: `- **status:** tracked → T-LX-##`
  4. **Leave genuinely open notes.** Future work threads (SCAN re-anchoring, heartbeat drift, category wiring) stay as-is with `status: open`.
  5. After cleanup, the file should contain ONLY: frontmatter, heading, description, Up link, and open/tracked notes.
  
  **Current open notes to cross-reference:**
  
  | Layer | Note | Task ID |
  |---|---|---|
  | L3 | Codex hardcode in discord/chat-flow.md | T-L3-05 |
  | L3 | L1 media.md config snippets may drift | none — informational, leave open |
  | L4 | SCAN re-anchoring needed | none — future (needs L5 trigger) |
  | L4 | Heartbeat drift detection | none — future (needs drift-guardian eval) |
  | L5 | Token budget exposure from L4 | T-L4-02 (partial) |
  | L5 | SCAN re-anchoring (acknowledges L4) | none — future |
  | L5 | Category blocks ready for wiring | none — future |
  | L6 | SCAN re-anchoring (acknowledges L4/L5) | none — future |
  | L6 | Heartbeat drift detection (acknowledges L4) | none — future |
  
